reviewText: I saw this concert in person and was absolutely blown away. There is no other artist on this planet who can put on as amazing of a concert as Cher. Watching is like watching Cirque du Soliel mixed with an ultra-vibrant, flamboyantly amazing Broadway show topped of with all the glitz and glam of the Cher universe. In this concert, Cher mostly sings her greatest hits. She changes sets and costumes (and wigs, and jewelry, and shoes) almost every song, creating a neverending and fascinating visual experience. Cher looks amazing, and to put it simply... she rocked everyone in that audience and will rock everyone who watches the DVD. There's nothing quite like Cher so you'll have to see it to believe it. Granted, this DVD isn't like being in the audience, but it's definitely a must-see. Even if you're not the biggest fan of her music, you'll be absolutely amazed at the spectacularness and visual quality of her sets and costumes and background dancers and singers, who are very much a part of her show as well. An absolutely amazing experience. I only have one warning: If you ever plan on going to a non-Cher concert and intend to have an amazing time, then don't watch this concert! Cher's concert is so incredible that it will probably spoil any other concert you might ever see. Nothing and nobody will ever live up to Cher- as she herself proudly proclaims. This may be Cher's last tour, but she most certainly will live forever! "Follow this, you ------s!"
summary: The one... the only... the incredible CHER

reviewText: Bought it recently and regret having not bought it sooner. Cher brings out the best in everyone, whether she sings or speaks onstage. I like her stage presence and her outlook on life. True, she is not going to tour anymore, but she will have left a great impact on young women in the music industry of the future (hopefully). It's hard to believe Cher has been a Diva for 40 years. She's got the body & soul of a 20-year-old, and I hope she won't go off the screen for good! She should continue acting, as I don't think the world will ever see enough of Cher.I missed both Montreal performances from this Tour, thinking it would be an utter waste of money. I was proven very wrong!Okay...regarding the DVD itself, here are some comments:Positive:- The Sound is amazing- The Costumes and Set Designs are much more stunning- The "If I could turn back time" performance blew me away! (she looks the same as in the 80's!)- Cher's dialogue on stage is really witty & entertaining- Her voice never gave out during the show- "Believe" was performed far better this time than on the "Believe Tour" DVD- I appreciate the extras and the interviews & backstage stuff (we learn more about Cher that way)- the costume changes (all 7 of them) were pretty quick!Negative:- Should've been a 2 disc set with Bonus Features on disc 2- The bonus songs in the "Bonus Features" should've been in the  show's tracklist- Cher didn't talk as much during this show, compared to the "Believe" tour DVDTRACKLIST:01- Opening02- I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For03- Song For The Lonely04- Gayatri Mantra05- All Or Nothing06- I Found Someone07- Bang Bang08- Sonny & Cher Medley (The Beat Goes On/Baby Don't Go/I Got You Babe)09- All I Really Want To Do (Medley Part 1)10- Half Breed (Medley Part 2)11- Gypsies, Tramps And Thieves (Medley Part 3)12- Dark Lady (Medley Part 4)13- Take Me Home14- The Way Of Love15- After All16- Just Like Jesse James17- Heart Of Stone18- The Shoop Shoop Song19- Strong Enough20- If I Could Turn Back Time21- Believe22- End CreditsBONUS FEATURES:- 3 Extra Live Songs From The Same Concert: (Save Up All Your Tears/ We All Sleep Alone/ A Different Kind of Love Song)- Music Video for "If I could Turn Back Time" 2003 Re-Edit- Cher's special version of "West Side Story"- Behind the scenes Documentary & Interviews- Extra Cher Monologues- Costume DesignsTotal Running Time: 92 MinutesI love the packaging. It's more compact and is very colorful. Cher is all about fun, and what she's given us is pure fun fun FUN! I've never imagined the DVD being as great as it is. So, i was very mistaken when I popped it into my mom's new DVD player. It blew us away! Cher belts out every song with power, grace and devotion to her career.Imagine doing 7 costume changes during a concert, looking even better with each one! It's amazing and very clever! Cher has a way with costumes and everything she does, making this Tour a true success! I love this concert much more than Sarah Brightman's "Harem Live in Las Vegas" DVD. There's just much more to enjoy and remember.For any Cher fan old & new...I highly recommend "Farewell Tour" to you. Buy it and relive 40 years of incredible music history by the most incredible Diva on earth!

reviewText: I was actually there in Miami for this taping.  Cher put on quite a show.  But it was that, a show.  Perfectly orchestrated, Cirque du Soleil style.  Very perfect and calculated and rehearsed, down to every line she said.But the real concert was the opening act, Cyndi Lauper.  She sounded amazing combining her old-time hits with her new songs.  Running through the audience and shaking hands with them, singing into people's cell phones.  By the time she started hitting stratospheric high notes during extended rendition of "Money Changes Everything", everybody was on their feet, screaming in ecstasy.What a concert!  Who needs dancers and special effects when you have the best voice in Pop music, a kick-ass band and enough energy to electrify a stadium.  BTW, she's taping her own concert on March 11 in NYC.  I can't wait for that one to be released.[...]Oh! and about the Madonna argument.  Cher did have another #1 with "I Got You Babe".  And Mariah Carey has 16 #1 hits which beat Madonna's 12.  Diana Ross has 18 but twelve of those are credited to The Supremes.  And as for sales in the US, Barbra Streissand is the number one seller with over 71.5 million  albums sold beating Madonna's 60 million.  Worldwide Madonna most likely is the winner, though.Madonna is amazing for many reasons.  You have to compare apples to apples.  Cher has an Oscar to her name and hosted a top TV show for years.  I don't think Madonna could ever do that.
summary: The REAL concert was the opening act

reviewText: Cher has been singing for over 40 years and she did it very good and I think that she'll continue doing it. So in 2002 she decided to start what it was going to be her Farewell Tour.This show is similar as her 2000 Believe Tour but with more production and quality (with this I'm not saying that it was bad, it was very good actually but this is way much better).On this show you can see Cher performing all her hits plus others that were on the program but weren't added to the final cut of the concert that was recorded in the American Airlines Arena in Miami Beach. As every Cher show you'll see lots of costumes changing, specail effects, lots of dancers and all Cher's Extravaganza. She has been very clever doing it now that she can do it very good without showing weakness of any kind.Some of the songs here are her #1's "Gypsies, tramps and thieves", "Dark lady", "Half-breed" and "Believe" plus her other hits like "If I could turn back time", "Just like Jesse James", "I found someone" and "Song for the lonely".She covered once again as the opening number U2's "I still  haven't found what I'm looking for" (which honestly sounds better on her).And finally among the special features you'll find the new "If I could turn back time" video, 3 extra live songs, Cher's special version of West Side Story (not big deal) and behind the scenes.Very good Cher you did it again.

reviewText: I never really considered Cher as an artist to recon with - oh well, I new the hits, and I even liked quite a few of them, but I never really took her seriously. However, this show, with it loads of everything-but-serious extravaganza, actually proves her to be a very good singer, and an entertainer that deserves huge respect.First ... make an experiment: Put on this DVD, without turning on your TV set, just listen to the music (or take the seperate CD release with the music from the show). What is easily forgotten in all the costume changes and wigs is, that this live performance is really amazing. This is all live, and Cher does an amazing vocal performance - and her full band plays without a single error. Most of the songs performed here are actually way better than the studio versions (highlights are All Or Nothing, I Found Someone, Bang Bang, All I Really Want To Do, The Way Of Love, After All, Just Like Jesse James, The Shoop Shoop Song and Believe). She actually performs U2's I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For better than U2 - and yes, I'm a fan of U2. Also, 3 bonus songs are added, which are all great - We All Sleep Alone is a favorite of mine.However, the visuals of this show is a complete world in it's own. Seven full costume changes are performed ('full' meaning everything from top to bottom including the wig is changed), and I won't even try to describe the costumes - fancyfull is too bland a word to use in this context. Minimalistic, if only in size and not in looks, is not beside the point, however. Imagine your 60 year old grandma turning up in an outfit consisting only of pailletes on strings, and which you could probably hold in your fisted hand. Well ... I can't help quote her from an earlier performance: "My mother told me, that when I was 2 years old I use to run around naked and sing ... And now I do it for a living."But this is Cher, and she gets away with it - probably because she considers herself with a lot of irony and humor - her monologues to the audience are simply fabulous, and had me howling with laughter. Let me quote: "We have to have these costume changes, cause otherwise drag queens all over the world will be calling each other tomorrow, saying 'I saw the Cher show last night - no costume changes, no wigs ... Do you think she's lost the will to live?'." And no, she deffenitely hasn't, as she concludes.The stage show is nothing but spectacular - dancers on the stage as well as above it, acrobats, an animated elephant, you name it, it's there. And lots of clips from movies and videos on the giant screen above the stage - enough to keep a dozen of eyes occupied without any of them seing the same thing. She wanted to make, not the greatest show, but the Cherest show on earth, and she deffenitely succeded.The sound on this release is unfortunately the one very weak spot - I guess that's why they released the CD to accompagny the DVD. The sound mix is horrible - I don't know whoever did it, but that person ought to start looking for another job immediately. The sound is fine most of the time, but each time the music gets more quite, the volume on the vocals gets extremely high. This happens quite a lot of times during the show, and it sounds awfull.The extras are great - not only does it include 3 songs not featured in the TV broadcasted version of the concert (Save Up All Your Tears, We All Sleep Alone and A Different Kind Of Love Song) but also her remake of The West Side Story in which she does - of course - star in all the roles. Go figure ... this is hilarious.In conclusion, this DVD captures Cher at her best, and everybody interested in the music of the last 50 years should have this DVD - after seeing this, you no longer are in doubt why she managed to be a central figure in showbussiness for 40 years (!). The show is quite probably unlike anything we will ever see again, and it is with a certain amount of regret that we say goodbye to Cher with this DVD, cause who could ever really take her place? As the diva says herself: "There are all these young girls coming along to take ... well, they are not going to take my place, but they are coming to take somebody's place ... Britney, J.Lo or whatever they're called."Rating: 9/10 (One point sadly lost due to lousy sound mix)
summary: I laughed at Cher, but this show desserves full respect.

reviewText: Cher's "Farewell Tour" DVD was filmed in Miami, Florida and was originally an NBC television special. In this concert, billed as Cher's final concert tour, the diva proves why she has been in the business for over forty years and why she has staying power. She performs songs that she is most famous for, everything from the old Sonny and Cher classics, to her early seventies material like "Half Breed", to her oustanding comeback song "Believe". If you are a true Cher fan you cannot miss out on owning one of the greatest concert specials ever filmed. From the music, to Cher's beautiful Bob Mackie costumes, to Cher's various wig hairstyles, this lady is the ultimate diva. Another great part of the concert is seeing Cher's interaction with the audience, an audience who has proven their love for her over and over.The DVD is filled with bonus features including three songs deleted from the special including her smash hit "Save Up All Your Tears", the music video "If I Could Turn Back Time", a documentary, interviews, and much more.
summary: "An Iconic Superstar Of The Highest Magnitude!"

reviewText: The colour, the audio and the chorography all come together in a splashy exciting bold show. Cher is amazing,never showing anything but love and enthusiasm for her effort here. The dvd has many exciting features,including a very informative documentary.Cher is in great voice, and showcased perfectly.This can't be a real farewell, as she is just too vital of a performer, the real entertainer to survive the 60's generation.Sonny would be proud and jealous too!
summary: This is the Cher-est Show on Earth

reviewText: I went into watching this concert with some reservation, but was pleasantly surprised.  Cher's costume changes, and impressive songlist make this a must-own DVD.  The only song I don't think she should include is the U2 cover of "I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For", this song does not work for Cher.I thoroughly enjoyed the 'history' part of the show where Cherdresses like she did in the 70's and performs her hits from then as part of a medley.  Cher still looks exactly the same as she did, so dressing up like that really works well.  I also loved it when the medley moved into her 1979 disco hit "take me Home".  Cher appeared in a carbaret outfit for this, simply stunning!  Then the song "The Way of Love" was performed, and Cher reappeared looking like she did in the mid 70's with very long straight black hair and an elegant slinky gown.  This performance alone, is worth the price of the DVD.If all of this wasn't enough, Cher does more costume changes for the "If I could turn back time" song, and yes, she really pulls this off beautifully.Love her, or hate her, you cannot deny that Cher is one of the true survivors.  I have the utmost respect for an artist that continually reinvents themselves, but does not forget any of their past.This concert is an absolute pleasure to watch.  I highly recommend it to see how a true performer puts on a show.  Well done Cher. I only wish the concert was longer.
summary: Excellent performance, I was pleasantly surprised
